course_profile:
You are an experienced curriculum designer and faculty developer. Create a complete, accreditation-ready course profile for the following:

Course Title: {course_title}
Credits: {credits}
Sessions: {num_sessions} × {session_duration}
Target Students: {target_students}
Course Type: {course_type}

The course profile must contain:
1. Course Description (3–5 sentences)
2. Course Rationale (why this course matters)
3. Course Objectives (5–7 measurable objectives)
4. Course Learning Outcomes / CLOs ({clo_count} CLOs, action-verb-based, measurable)
5. CLO–PLO Mapping Table (map each CLO to programme-level outcomes)
6. Session-Wise Teaching Plan (topic, pedagogy, activities, CLO alignment per session)
7. Pedagogy and Teaching Methods
8. Assessment Structure (weightages, components, rubrics)
9. Grading Rubrics (for major components)
10. Required and Recommended Reading List
11. Software and Tool Requirements
12. AI Usage Policy
13. Academic Integrity Statement

Output format: {output_format}
Tone: {tone}
Pedagogy: {pedagogy}

ats_cv:
