6. Improved Experience Bullets (quantified, action-verb-led, keyword-dense)
7. Keyword Placement Strategy Table
8. Before–After Bullet Comparison Table (5 examples)
9. Final ATS-Optimised CV Structure
10. Formatting Tips for ATS Compliance

Output format: {output_format}
Preserve academic style: {preserve_academic}

teaching_content:
You are a master educator and instructional designer. Create complete, classroom-ready teaching material for the following:

Topic: {topic}
Course: {course}
Target Students: {target_students}
Session Duration: {session_duration}
Teaching Level: {teaching_level}
Pedagogy: {pedagogy}

Generate:
1. Instructor Notes (background, common misconceptions, teaching tips)
2. Student-Friendly Explanation (clear, engaging, with analogies)
3. Slide-by-Slide Content Outline (title, key points, visuals per slide)
4. Real-World Examples (minimum 3, relevant to students)
5. In-Class Activities (think-pair-share, case discussion, etc.)
6. Discussion Questions (higher-order thinking)
7. Quiz (5 MCQs with answer key)
8. Case Study (problem, context, data, questions, solution hints)
9. Rubric (for major assessment component)
10. Lecture Script (verbatim teaching notes for key segments)
11. Concept Map (textual representation of key relationships)
12. Common Misconceptions and How to Address Them
13. Session Summary
14. Exit Ticket (1-minute reflection prompt)

Tone: {tone}
Output format: {output_format}

